      "message": "@spinler@us.ibm.com\n\nI checked how these values are populated and found that they are not\nfixed constants—they are derived from Yocto configuration.\n\nFor example, `error_info_cap` is computed via\n`get_info_cap(d)` based on FLASH_SIZE and can also be\noverridden (e.g., via `ERR_INFO_CAP` and EXTRA_OEMESON).\n\nSo the final value (128 in my build) is platform-dependent,\nnot constant. Similar applies to other values like\n`redundant-bmc` and `lg2_commit_strategy`.\n\nGiven this, hardcoding them would remove intended\nconfigurability.",
